{"word":"H4549 - מָסַס - mâçaç - maw-sas' - Discourage","slug":"H4549","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">מָסַס</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>mâçaç"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>maw-sas'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Discourage"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05DE;&#x05E1;&#x05E1; - ma&#x0302;sas</b> - <i>maw-sas'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>liquefy</i>; figuratively to <i>waste</i> (with disease), to <i>faint</i> (with fatigue, fear or grief): - discourage, faint, be loosed, melt (away), refuse, X utterly."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H4523\">H4523</a>, <a href=\"#/H4531\">H4531</a>, <a href=\"#/H8557\">H8557</a>"}]}